  "body": "If you try to use `debug_traceTransaction` in an unsupported network, you'll get a message like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nNetwork id 42161 does not correspond to a network that Hardhat can trace\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis isn't very helpful, because if you add the proper `chains` configuration, then `debug_tt` will work.\r\n\r\nWe are receiving a more useful error here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/727740f8e7bdcfca1cb8e6b89e34744306f0e976/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts#L2684\r\n\r\nSo maybe it would be enough to add it as the parent error of the thrown internal error.",
